title.narrative: National Initiatives for Sustainable & Climate Smart oil Palm Smallholders Nigeria

description.narrative: In Nigeria, working with 12,000 smallholder farmers (approx. 20% of registered smallholder farmers in Nigeria), NI-SCOPS setup Multi Stakeholder Platforms at community and Local Government levels with 2 Committees to coordinate community-based land use planning, and Sustainable Management Plans and Policy Coordination. The project also secured private sector funding support from Henkel and from Releaf MarketPlace International.
